/**
 * \page yac_tools YAC tools

All YAC tools are \ref installing_yac "built" together with
the \ref yac_libs.

The `*.x`-tools can be found in `<yac_build_dir>/tools` and the `*.py`-tools
int `<yac_repo_dir>/tools`.

One major task of the tools is the
\ref weight_files "visualisation of weight files", which is essential for
analysing and debugging of interpolation generated by YAC.

\section debug_grid2vtk debug_grid2vtk.x

This tool turns grid-files generated by YAC using the
\ref yaml_file "configuration file" `output_grids` debug option into a
vtk-file, which can easily be visualised using
<a href="https://www.paraview.org/">Paraview</a>.

\section weights2vtk weights2vtk.x

Based on weight files created by YAC, this tool can generate a VTK-file, which
can be used to visualise weights using
<a href="https://www.paraview.org/">Paraview</a>.<br>
(for more Information see \ref weight_files)

\section grid_utils grid_utils.py

Contains functionallity for handling grid files in Python.

\section plot_weights plot_weights.py

Tool for plotting weights and weight stencils from YAC-created weight files.<br>
(for more Information see \ref weight_files)

\section record_replay yac_record.py & yac_replay.py

Tools for recording data in a coupled setup and write the data to a
netCDF file. This recordings can then be used to replay the data in a
coupled setup and use the replay component as a source. <br>
For detailed explanation see \ref record_replay_page.

\section yac_compute_weights yac_compute_weights.x

This tool allows the user to easily generate
interpolation weights for the remapping between two grids and write them to
file. The grid information can be provided via a grid file (multiple formats
are supported) or YAC can generate it based on user specifications. The
interpolation is freely configurable via a JSON-formatted command line argument
and follows the defintion of the \ref interp_stack "interpolation stack" in the
configuration file.<br>
The tool is MPI-parallel and can be run with an arbitrary number of processes. <br>
(for more Information see \ref yac_compute_weights_page)

<hr>

\subpage record_replay_page "Recording and Replaying Coupling Data"
\subpage weight_files "Weight files"
\subpage yac_compute_weights_page


*/
